<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-348] document adding a second network to an existing filesystem</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-348</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There needs to be clear documentation with an example in the user manual on how to add a second network to an existing filesystem.  There are often requests to add a second LNet network (e.g. add TCP network for IB filesystem, or vice versa) and having this clearly described with exact examples would ensure that users can find this information easily.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This should probably go into section &lt;tt&gt;15.3. Multi-Rail Configurations with LNET&lt;/tt&gt; with a reference from &lt;tt&gt;14. Lustre Maintenance&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
